      "id": "1548f52e-2a88-4b13-a667-7e2d37639b5f",
      "name": "puzzles AI",
      "developer": "loganathanm.in",
      "shortDescription": "Pinch, drag & solve puzzles with your hand — no touch needed! AI-powered fun.",
      "description": "Step-by-Step Guide\n\n1. Open the website\nGo to https://puzzle.loganathanm.in/ on a device with a camera (laptop/desktop with webcam works best).\n\n2. Wait for the AI engine to load\nYou'll see \"INITIALIZING AI ENGINE...\" — this is the AI loading up to detect your hand movements. Give it a few seconds.\n\n3. Choose difficulty\nSelect Easy (3x3) to start with a simple 3x3 grid puzzle.\n\n4. Allow camera access\nThe browser will ask for camera permission — click Allow, since the game tracks your hand through the webcam.\n\n5. Tap \"START GAME\"\nThis begins the puzzle round.\n\n6. Control the cursor with your hand\nMove your hand in front of the camera — the on-screen cursor follows your hand movement.\n\n7. Pick up a puzzle piece\nPinch your fingers together and hold (like a pinch gesture) over the piece you want to move.\n\n8. Drag and swap\nWhile still pinching, move your hand to drag the piece to a new position, then release the pinch to drop/swap it with another piece.\n\n9. Repeat until solved\nKeep pinching, dragging, and releasing pieces until the full image/puzzle is correctly arranged.\n\n10. Check the Leaderboard\nAfter playing, tap LEADERBOARD to see your ranking/score compared to other players\n\n\n\nTips:\n\n1. Sit in a well-lit area so the camera can track your hand clearly.\n2. Keep your hand within the camera frame the whole time.\n3. If gestures aren't registering, try moving your hand a bit slower and closer to the camera.",
